Full Description: WambaTech came kicking and screaming into this world, conceived by a passion to innovate and a dash of mania. Their brave CEO, Nat Plane, believed he could build a lead engine superior to the one he had been supporting as a developer. Turns out he wasn’t just being cocky. Soon he had oodles of clients signing on for what would be their flagship product, WambaTech Lead Server. The whole fam-damily got in on the madness. Nat’s dad and two brothers joined force, making essential their own design, networking, and development skillsets. Two years later, WambaTech had its first contract with a major entity to build a custom lead-processing solution for Lincoln and Ford nameplates. Add 12 height marks to the wall and they are a tween! Their family has expanded six-fold and now composes a full-suite custom-software .NET shop. They are one of very few in their home state of Michigan. their specializations include all forms of digital marketing, and custom data management and processing applications. Specifically, that means enhancement of hundreds of websites, email and other social media marketing, as well as architecture and maintenance for lead-processing systems, data normalization and validation programs, consumer data management products, inventory tracking platforms, administrative data portals, and more. Their Detroit Metro-based team is their greatest asset, most of them with interdisciplinary technology skillsets and domain knowledge crossing markets. While others may need weeks on that estimate, they huddle up and turn around flexible, comprehensive solutions at breakneck pace. Their pride comes from their agility, innovation, accuracy, and their consultative nature. Their satisfaction comes from over-delivering, outperforming, and trying to be heroes.

Description: Tappy Technology is a smart city technology that helps cities and its transportation systems become smarter for people with disabilities.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Tappy Technology is a smart city technology that helps cities, it's infrastructures, businesses and transportation systems become smarter for people with disabilities. Transportation is defined as the movement of people and goods from Point A to Point B. But, how does an individual with a disability navigate to, or even identify Point A? What happens to them after arriving close to Point B if their mode of transportation does not complete their journey? One of mobility’s toughest challenges for an individual with a disability is providing a safe and simple solution to the First Mile/Last Mile navigation problem. Riders with a disability struggle to travel this short distance to or from a transit stop and points of interest because of physical or other limitations. Tappy Guide mobile application, provides navigation to help locate and identify pick-up and drop-off locations, and building entrances and exits. The user-friendly technology eliminates the First Mile/Last Mile navigation problem such as true, point-to-point, demand-response service.

Description: Resource Central is a non-profit organization that helps people save water, reduce waste, and conserve energy.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: At Resource Central, our mission is to revolutionize the way we think about waste and sustainability. We firmly believe that even the smallest actions can have a tremendous impact on creating a cleaner, greener planet to call home. That's why we've established a one-of-a-kind community facility designed specifically for contractors, homeowners, and businesses with a commitment to zero waste. Our goal is to make it easy for you to donate building materials, construction materials, and building supplies. By choosing to donate these materials instead of discarding them, you're not only helping to reduce waste, but also extending a helping hand to those in need of affordable supplies for their own building projects. And as a token of our gratitude, you'll also be eligible for a tax deduction for your generous donation. Inside our facility, you'll discover a treasure trove of reclaimed items that have been diligently inspected and sorted to guarantee their quality and usability. Whether you're in search of sturdy lumber, beautiful cabinets, doors, windows, plumbing fixtures, or electrical supplies - we have it all. Regardless of the reason behind your surplus materials - whether it's a home renovation, rental property management, or simply clearing out clutter during a spring cleaning spree - we strongly encourage you to consider donating them to us. Your contribution will not only divert waste away from landfills, but also help to conserve valuable natural resources and bolster our ongoing sustainability initiatives. In addition to accepting donations, we also invite you to explore our facility and shop for an impressive array of reclaimed materials. By opting to purchase these items, you'll actively support our cause and play a vital role in reducing the demand for brand new resources. And the best part? You'll get to acquire high-quality materials at incredibly affordable prices. If you're looking for a meaningful way to have a positive impact on the environment and contribute to waste reduction efforts, look no further than Resource Central. Join us in our mission to construct a brighter, greener future for our community and beyond. Reach out to us today to learn more about how you can get involved and make a real difference.
